  "notes": [
    "Every packet was sealed by the exact producer revision with fixed synthetic key, ephemeral, timestamp, counter, preamble, body, and cookie inputs; independent consumers must rebuild initiator packets and authenticate-open replies.",
    "The merged producer intentionally echoes the NHP_KNK counter in NHP_COK for relay compatibility, as frozen here, but native UDP consumers must treat the authenticated COK wire counter as unconstrained and correlate only when decrypted trxId equals the originating NHP_KNK counter. The accept_cok_wire_counter_unconstrained flow mutation proves that consumer rule. NHP_ACK counters must echo NHP_RKN or NHP_EXT.",
    "The NHP_RKN header digest mixes the exact decoded 32-byte cookie after the ordinary header prefix. NHP_EXT uses the ordinary no-cookie digest and its authenticated body headerType must equal the outer type.",
    "Each successful NHP_ACK resHost, acTokens, and preActions map contains exactly one entry keyed by the session resId.",
    "All identities, hosts, keys, cookies, counters, and tokens are synthetic conformance data."
  ],
